page.title: 14 ECOLOGY
page.content: We examined the hedgerows in our area. We found many common wild flowers including:- Fern, Tormantil, Dogrose, Dandelion, Daisy, Buttercup, Cowparsley, Hogweed, Juniper, Shepherd's Purse, Creeping Buttercup,Purple Vetch,Plantain, Honeysuckle, Pink Campion, Scarlet Pimpernal, Goose Grass, Papratensis, ivy and hogweed. The hedgerows were steeply banked with large and small trees growing in them - including English Oak, Field Maple and Ash. We noticed many flies, grasshoppers, spiders and bees and we saw a small bush 4ft by 5ft completely covered in spiders'webs. One Cabbage White butterfly, blackbirds, pheasants, rabbits moved through the hedgerow area.
